      ],
      "ignore": false,
      "order": "8",
      "anno_id": 1,
      "text": " where the minimum runs over the orthogonal group  $O(n)$ . Then  $Iso(K)$  is upper bounded. In fact, denoting by  $\\Delta_n$  an  $i$ -simplex, Ball has proved :",
      "line_with_spans": [
