      "text": " Denote  $V_n(L_1, ..., L_n)$  the mixed volume of  $n$  convex bodies, and denote  $V_n(K) = V(K[n])$  the volume of  $K$ . Since  $|\\partial K|_{n-1} = nV_n(K[n-1], B_2^n)$ , where  $B_2^n$  denotes the (unit)  $\\ell_2$ -ball in  $\\mathbb{R}^n$ , Ball's result can be reformulated within the language of mixed volumes as follows: for any convex body  $K \\subset \\mathbb{R}^n$ , there exists an ellipsoid  $\\mathcal{E}$ , such that",
